Tanon et al. [pellissier2017completeness] use cardinality information to improve rule-mining. Rule mining is the task of finding interesting associations between entities in a KB, such as: if \fact{?x}{hasSpouse}{?y} and \fact{?y}{livesIn}{?z} then \fact{?x}{livesIn}{?z}. Such rules can then be used to predict the place of residence of someone.